Esca.FarmTypeManager.Config.EnableConsoleCommands.Name: Enable console commands
Esca.FarmTypeManager.Config.EnableConsoleCommands.Desc:
Enables FTM's console commands.
This will not take effect until Stardew Valley is restarted.
Esca.FarmTypeManager.Config.EnableContentPacks.Name: Enable content packs
Esca.FarmTypeManager.Config.EnableContentPacks.Desc:
Enables all FTM content packs.
If this is disabled, only the files in FarmTypeManager/data will be used.
Esca.FarmTypeManager.Config.EnableTraceLogMessages.Name: Enable trace log messages
Esca.FarmTypeManager.Config.EnableTraceLogMessages.Desc:
Enables FTM's [TRACE] messages in SMAPI's log files.
If this is disabled, log files will be smaller, but they'll provide less information about FTM.
Esca.FarmTypeManager.Config.EnableEPUDebugMessages.Name: Enable EPU debug messages
Esca.FarmTypeManager.Config.EnableEPUDebugMessages.Desc:
Enables Expanded Preconditions Utility (EPU) debug messages.
This can be helpful when creating mods with preconditions.
Esca.FarmTypeManager.Config.MonsterLimitPerLocation.Name: Monster limit per location
Esca.FarmTypeManager.Config.MonsterLimitPerLocation.Desc:
The maximum number of monsters FTM will allow on a single map simultaneously.
Using a lower number can improve the game's framerate. 50 is a common suggestion.
Type NULL to allow unlimited monsters.
